## Basics

- **HTML basics**
    
    1 element = Opening tag + Content/Child element + Closing tag 
    
    - *119 types of elements*
    - *C√≥ lo·∫°i ko c√≥ content ho·∫∑c t·ª± ƒë√≥ng nh∆∞ `<br>, <embed>, <img src="x.gif" />`*
    - `index.html` =  default name of 1st page every web
    - `<!DOCTYPE html>` = ƒê√°nh d·∫•u ƒë√¢y l√† vƒÉn b·∫£n HTML
    - `lang=‚Äùen‚Äù` ‚Üí set up language
    - `<head>` ‚Üí invisible, nh∆∞ title, link CSS‚Ä¶
        - `<meta charset=UTF-8‚Äù />` ‚Üí setup character & meta data
        - `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">`
            - `width=device-width`¬†part sets the width of the page to follow the screen-width of the device
            - `initial-scale=1.0`¬†part sets the initial zoom level when the page is first loaded by the browser.
    - `<body>` ‚Üí visible
    
    `<hr>`
    
    - horizontal line (divider)
    - like `<br>` to break
- Emphasize
    - Comment `<!-- -->`
    - Bold `<b>` ‚Üí no meaning
        - `<strong>` ‚Üí standout meaning
    - Italic `<i>` ‚Üí no meaning
        - `<em>` ‚Üí emphasized meaning
- Semantic
    
    (Descriptive) tags for SEO 
    
    - X∆∞a: *****`<div id="nav"> <div class="header"> <div id="footer">`*
        - `div` hay `span`  ‚Üí no meaning
    - Nay *`main, header, footer, nav, video, article, section‚Ä¶`*
        - B·∫£n ch·∫•t ko kh√°c g√¨ div nh∆∞ng gi√∫p d·ªÖ ƒë·ªçc h∆°n, SEO & Accessibility
        - `nav` c√≥ th·ªÉ l√† `section`
        - `header` ko ƒë∆∞·ª£c n·∫±m trong `footer`
            - <main> gi·ªØa header & footer
            - 1 page ch·ªâ 1 main
        - `<aside>` ‚Üí sidebar menu
    - Structure
    
